 by various investigators and propose that these\nmeasurements may improve theoretical models. We interpret the variation of both\nEp and w with temperature as due to the changes in the ionization and\nrecombination conditions in the plasma during the flare interval and as a\nconsequence the contribution from different ionic emission lines also varies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Dec 2006 21:00:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
