 greater than $\\sim 10$ Gyr. Therefore, for globular\nclusters as old as the majority of the Galactic GCs, our method do not\ndistinguish them accurately. We emphasize that our results show that even with\nmultiband photometry spanning NUV to $K_s$, our age constraints from SED\nfitting are distressingly uncertain, which has implications for age derivations\nin extragalactic globular cluster systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Dec 2006 05:51:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-02-11"}
